WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:11.177
[scribbling]

2
00:00:12.971 --> 00:00:14.389
[scribbling]

3
00:00:17.017 --> 00:00:18.101
[upbeat music playing]

4
00:00:18.184 --> 00:00:20.395
[Isla] I never had a lot
of female friends growing up.

5
00:00:20.478 --> 00:00:22.981
My mother taught me
all women were threats.

6
00:00:23.064 --> 00:00:26.943
So it wasn't until college
when I made my first real girlfriend.

7
00:00:27.027 --> 00:00:28.820
but boy. did she hate me.

8
00:00:28.903 --> 00:00:30.572
What the fuck. Isla?

9
00:00:30.655 --> 00:00:34.034
You passed out drunk
with the hot plate on my bed again.

10
00:00:34.117 --> 00:00:36.619
[Isla] She eventually accepted
my Cali girl charm.

11
00:00:36.703 --> 00:00:41.458
and somehow this angry little Chicago "B"
became my closest girlfriend.

12
00:00:41.541 --> 00:00:43.418
Best birthday ever.

13
00:00:43.501 --> 00:00:44.544
[Isla] Mm-hmm.

14
00:00:44.627 --> 00:00:46.796
These taste just like
the ones from Wrigley.

15
00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:48.798
Well. that's 'cause they are.

16
00:00:48.882 --> 00:00:50.383
Sammy Sosa is a family friend.

17
00:00:50.467 --> 00:00:51.342
What?

18
00:00:51.426 --> 00:00:52.719
♪ Do it. whoo♪

19
00:00:52.802 --> 00:00:54.012
[both sobbing]

20
00:00:54.095 --> 00:00:55.180
[girl on TV] His face hurts.

21
00:00:55.263 --> 00:00:57.682
[both crying] He can't see
without his glasses.

22
00:00:57.766 --> 00:00:58.975
[Isla] We were inseparable.

23
00:00:59.059 --> 00:01:00.685
[Isla screams. cheers]

24
00:01:00.769 --> 00:01:03.480
[both] Chug. chug. chug. chug.

25
00:01:03.563 --> 00:01:04.439
[Isla and Ali scream]

26
00:01:04.522 --> 00:01:08.318
[Isla] Our college friendship turned into
a beautiful working relationship…

27
00:01:08.401 --> 00:01:09.235
-[laughs]
-It's true.

28
00:01:09.319 --> 00:01:11.863
…until she decided to betray me
to go work for another team…

29
00:01:11.946 --> 00:01:12.947
Do we have a deal?

30
00:01:13.031 --> 00:01:14.783
…in the most boring place on earth.

31
00:01:14.866 --> 00:01:17.077
Are you seriously going to Toronto?

32
00:01:17.160 --> 00:01:19.954
I have to. Magnus offered me
a promotion and more money.

33
00:01:20.038 --> 00:01:22.791
-I know you can't match it.
-So this is about the office and raise?

34
00:01:22.874 --> 00:01:26.252
Yes. Isla. it was about those things
I was promised but didn't get.

35
00:01:26.336 --> 00:01:28.922
You know. and more importantly.
it's about being valued.

36
00:01:29.005 --> 00:01:30.465
Of course I value you.

37
00:01:30.548 --> 00:01:31.883
You're my best friend.

38
00:01:31.966 --> 00:01:34.302
Well. then you should encourage me
to take this opportunity.

39
00:01:34.385 --> 00:01:35.887
What. and move to Canada?

40
00:01:35.970 --> 00:01:39.307
You're gonna freeze to death.
You use your seat heaters in July.

41
00:01:39.390 --> 00:01:43.228
I love Toronto. It's cool.
They just hosted a season of Top Chef.

42
00:01:43.311 --> 00:01:45.438
-That means nothing since Padma left.
-Oh.

43
00:01:45.522 --> 00:01:49.067
This is outrageous.
I can't believe you're doing this to me.

44
00:01:49.818 --> 00:01:50.819
To you?

45
00:01:51.361 --> 00:01:54.239
Have you ever considered
that I'm doing this for me?

46
00:01:54.906 --> 00:01:57.408
You know. probably not because
that's what a good friend would do.

47
00:01:57.492 --> 00:02:00.411
A good friend? You're my maid of honor.

48
00:02:00.495 --> 00:02:03.414
How are you supposed to do that
if you're thousands of miles away

49
00:02:03.498 --> 00:02:06.209
or millions of miles away
or wherever Toronto is?

50
00:02:06.292 --> 00:02:08.545
Well. apologies
for making a major life decision

51
00:02:08.628 --> 00:02:11.339
without keeping your
ever-changing wedding calendar in mind.

52
00:02:11.422 --> 00:02:14.551
[tense music playing]

53
00:02:14.634 --> 00:02:16.010
Sorry. that came out wrong.

54
00:02:16.094 --> 00:02:17.679
No. it's fine.

55
00:02:18.847 --> 00:02:20.807
Didn't realize I was such a burden.

56
00:02:20.890 --> 00:02:22.851
so don't worry
about being my maid of honor.

57
00:02:22.934 --> 00:02:27.021
I'll have one of my sisters-in-law do it.
So you're off the hook. Ali.

58
00:02:28.273 --> 00:02:29.357
Fine.

59
00:02:29.440 --> 00:02:30.275
Fine.

60
00:02:31.151 --> 00:02:32.694
[tense music ends]

61
00:02:32.777 --> 00:02:34.195
Well. if that's it then…

62
00:02:34.279 --> 00:02:35.697
[inhales deeply]

63
00:02:36.281 --> 00:02:37.282
…goodbye.

64
00:02:38.116 --> 00:02:39.576
-Bye.
-[Ali clears throat]

65
00:02:41.536 --> 00:02:42.412
Ness!

66
00:02:43.413 --> 00:02:47.458
Oh God.
Tell Bituin that she's been promoted.

67
00:02:47.542 --> 00:02:49.627
Well. I've actually been meaning
to tell you this.

68
00:02:49.711 --> 00:02:52.088
but Bituin doesn't want to be
in your bridal party.

69
00:02:52.589 --> 00:02:54.883
She refuses to wear matching dresses.

70
00:02:56.426 --> 00:02:57.552
♪ Breathe ♪

71
00:02:57.635 --> 00:02:59.179
♪ Ready for me ♪

72
00:02:59.262 --> 00:03:00.555
♪ Now watch me go get it. baby ♪

73
00:03:01.055 --> 00:03:02.348
♪ Hey ♪

74
00:03:02.432 --> 00:03:04.184
♪ Uh… ♪

75
00:03:04.267 --> 00:03:07.645
[announcer] It's been an exciting
opening night at Ally Bank Arena.

76
00:03:07.729 --> 00:03:10.273
but LA is trailing down the stretch.

77
00:03:11.566 --> 00:03:12.567
Oh. dammit.

78
00:03:12.650 --> 00:03:16.529
Hey. Isla… Isla. can I get Ali's seat?
I got mustard on mine.

79
00:03:16.613 --> 00:03:18.323
-No.
-I'm coming over.

80
00:03:18.406 --> 00:03:20.700
-Ugh. God. Ness.
-Here we go. Here we go.

81
00:03:20.783 --> 00:03:23.661
Look. I know it's only one game
and we're getting used to a new coach.

82
00:03:23.745 --> 00:03:26.831
-But this should've been an easy W.
-There's still time. okay. We got this.

83
00:03:26.915 --> 00:03:29.459
[announcer] Bugg surveys
at the top of the key.

84
00:03:29.542 --> 00:03:32.128
Travis drives.
He's gotta unload it. Dyson's open.

85
00:03:32.212 --> 00:03:33.087
[crowd cheers]

86
00:03:33.171 --> 00:03:36.799
Bugg swings it to Coburn
for an impossibly deep three.

87
00:03:36.883 --> 00:03:39.302
-[buzzer sounds]
-And LA drops the season opener.

88
00:03:39.385 --> 00:03:41.471
-Bugg had Dyson open under the basket.
-[whistle blows]

89
00:03:41.554 --> 00:03:43.473
Yo. bro. you ain't see me?
I was wide open.

90
00:03:43.556 --> 00:03:44.432
I saw you.

91
00:03:44.515 --> 00:03:46.601
-[Ness] I don't know how he missed him.
-[Norm] Wow.

92
00:03:46.684 --> 00:03:47.810
What the hell was that?

93
00:03:47.894 --> 00:03:48.853
He makes that shot.

94
00:03:48.937 --> 00:03:51.064
this whole crowd goes home
with curly fries.

95
00:03:52.440 --> 00:03:54.317
[upbeat music playing]

96
00:03:56.653 --> 00:03:58.863
[Charlie] Okay. Uh. great.
you'll email me my call time.

97
00:03:59.572 --> 00:04:00.907
Okay. thank you. [chuckles]

98
00:04:01.824 --> 00:04:03.243
Okay.

99
00:04:03.910 --> 00:04:06.537
Sounds like somebody got
their first big Hollywood gig.

100
00:04:06.621 --> 00:04:07.997
Well. don't get too excited.

101
00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:10.959
My. uh… my role is featured background
on a reality show.

102
00:04:11.042 --> 00:04:12.752
[inhales] We don't even get
the same crafty.

103
00:04:12.835 --> 00:04:16.673
Well. you know. it beats laying around
on the couch all day playing Minecraft.

104
00:04:16.756 --> 00:04:19.676
Well. I… Yeah. I just… I don't know.
I really wanted to do narrative.

105
00:04:19.759 --> 00:04:21.261
Like be on White Lotus or something.

106
00:04:21.344 --> 00:04:23.304
I think there might be a few steps

107
00:04:23.388 --> 00:04:26.766
in between former dog groomer
and star of The White Lotus.

108
00:04:26.849 --> 00:04:28.685
Not if you're young. hot.
and read straight.

109
00:04:28.768 --> 00:04:30.019
You read straight.

110
00:04:30.103 --> 00:04:32.563
-So I'm not young and hot?
-Neither of us are young.

111
00:04:32.647 --> 00:04:36.025
Look. all I'm saying is
that this is an opportunity.

112
00:04:36.109 --> 00:04:40.446
I mean. what if Mike White sees you
in this featured background role?

113
00:04:40.530 --> 00:04:43.199
Okay. Okay. I'll do it. I'll do it.

114
00:04:43.283 --> 00:04:45.493
Good. Great. Exciting.

115
00:04:45.576 --> 00:04:48.121
So not only
are the Waves off to a rocky start.

116
00:04:48.204 --> 00:04:51.082
we're also hearing rumors
of a love triangle

117
00:04:51.165 --> 00:04:54.085
that is threatening
to tear apart the locker room.

118
00:04:54.168 --> 00:04:55.253
Here's the deets.

119
00:04:55.336 --> 00:05:00.216
Dyson Gibbs has been getting serious
with sexy actress Zoé Debay

120
00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:05.096
who was previously linked. very briefly.
with his teammate Travis Bugg.

121
00:05:05.179 --> 00:05:06.889
Is this a throuple gone bad?

122
00:05:06.973 --> 00:05:09.475
As someone
who's been kicked out of a threesome.

123
00:05:09.559 --> 00:05:12.228
I can tell you
that is gonna sting for a while.

124
00:05:12.312 --> 00:05:15.064
How did we not know about this? Ness?

125
00:05:15.148 --> 00:05:17.984
'Cause Ali was always
the one on top of player gossip.

126
00:05:18.067 --> 00:05:19.944
They never realized
she was on their text chain.

127
00:05:20.028 --> 00:05:21.654
Yeah. she usually put out these fires.

128
00:05:21.738 --> 00:05:23.865
I mean. Ali's small.
but the players were scared of her.

129
00:05:23.948 --> 00:05:26.743
-Not just the players.
-Can we stop talking about my ex-friend?

130
00:05:26.826 --> 00:05:30.371
We've got to figure out
how to fix this Travis-Dyson feud.

131
00:05:30.455 --> 00:05:34.167
Is this gonna affect the sketch I wrote
with Travis and Dyson playing charades?

132
00:05:34.250 --> 00:05:35.251
You know what. Jackie?

133
00:05:35.335 --> 00:05:38.713
I love you more than anyone here.
but no one cares. We gotta Bluesky this.

134
00:05:39.297 --> 00:05:41.090
-What are you doing?
-Checking Bluesky.

135
00:05:41.174 --> 00:05:43.259
Seeing if anyone has any Zoé Debay goss.

136
00:05:43.343 --> 00:05:46.971
If this is a locker-room issue.
shouldn't the coach deal with it?

137
00:05:47.055 --> 00:05:50.141
Yes. Norm can fix this. Thank you. Sandy.

138
00:05:50.224 --> 00:05:54.020
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. I just found
an AI video of Dyson and Travis kissing.

139
00:05:54.604 --> 00:05:57.106
Wow. At least I think it's AI.

140
00:05:57.190 --> 00:05:59.150
but if not. problem solved.

141
00:05:59.233 --> 00:06:00.693
In women's hoop news.

142
00:06:00.777 --> 00:06:05.615
LA power forward Brielle Mande
has been suspended again.

143
00:06:05.698 --> 00:06:08.659
This time
for flipping the double bird to the crowd

144
00:06:08.743 --> 00:06:11.537
during Girl Scout Appreciation Night.

145
00:06:11.621 --> 00:06:13.164
What a crazy bitch.

146
00:06:13.247 --> 00:06:15.041
And before you try to cancel me.

147
00:06:15.124 --> 00:06:16.793
I have two daughters.

148
00:06:16.876 --> 00:06:19.003
-That's sweet. He's a girl dad.
-Blech!

149
00:06:19.087 --> 00:06:20.129
[upbeat music playing]

150
00:06:20.213 --> 00:06:22.006
[wind blowing]

151
00:06:25.593 --> 00:06:27.220
This is where the moose sausage gets made.

152
00:06:27.303 --> 00:06:30.390
-[Ali chuckles]
-You ready to meet and memorize 158 names?

153
00:06:30.473 --> 00:06:32.558
Oh. uh. sure. [chuckles]

154
00:06:32.642 --> 00:06:34.352
I'm kidding. There's only 113 of us.

155
00:06:34.435 --> 00:06:35.812
-[laughs softly]
-[Magnus laughs]

156
00:06:35.895 --> 00:06:37.021
Okay.

157
00:06:37.105 --> 00:06:37.980
Hi. y'all.

158
00:06:38.523 --> 00:06:43.194
This is the incredible Ali Lee. our new
Vice President of Basketball Operations.

159
00:06:43.277 --> 00:06:45.279
-[all applaud]
-[Ali] Oh.

160
00:06:46.280 --> 00:06:48.241
Hi. Uh. I can't wait to get started.

161
00:06:48.324 --> 00:06:50.076
I am so excited to be here.

162
00:06:50.159 --> 00:06:51.119
Go Trappers!

163
00:06:51.202 --> 00:06:53.329
-[Ali laughs nervously]
-[man] Hmm.

164
00:06:54.038 --> 00:06:56.165
[softly] It's "Goooo Trappers."

165
00:06:57.792 --> 00:06:59.252
-[softly] Oh. [chuckles]
-It's okay.

166
00:06:59.794 --> 00:07:01.129
-[Magnus] Come on.
-Oh.

167
00:07:01.212 --> 00:07:02.380
We've arrived.

168
00:07:02.463 --> 00:07:04.173
Your new home away from home.

169
00:07:05.925 --> 00:07:08.719
This is incredible.

170
00:07:08.803 --> 00:07:09.887
[Magnus] Mm-hmm.

171
00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:14.350
On a clear day.
you can see suburban Buffalo from here.

172
00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:15.351
[laughs softly]

173
00:07:16.102 --> 00:07:18.563
-You must be Ali Lee.
-Yes.

174
00:07:18.646 --> 00:07:20.106
-Welcome.
-Oh. thank you.

175
00:07:20.189 --> 00:07:23.359
I'm brewing a fresh pot of cocoa.
How do you take yours?

176
00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:27.071
Uh. with marshmallows and whipped cream.

177
00:07:27.155 --> 00:07:28.739
Oh. the whole shebang. eh?

178
00:07:28.823 --> 00:07:30.491
Of course you know Carl. our CEO.

179
00:07:30.575 --> 00:07:31.868
Oh. CEO.

180
00:07:32.368 --> 00:07:33.244
Let me guess.

181
00:07:33.327 --> 00:07:34.871
Cocoa executive officer?

182
00:07:34.954 --> 00:07:37.081
[all laugh]

183
00:07:39.667 --> 00:07:42.336
Magnus. you didn't tell me
you hired Jim Carrey.

184
00:07:42.420 --> 00:07:44.130
[imitating Jim Carrey] Somebody stop me.

185
00:07:44.213 --> 00:07:47.258
[all laugh]

186
00:07:48.759 --> 00:07:50.761
♪This one is for the dream ♪

187
00:07:51.554 --> 00:07:53.306
♪Yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah ♪

188
00:07:53.931 --> 00:07:56.058
♪This one is for the dream ♪

189
00:07:57.101 --> 00:08:00.271
Coach. we have an urgent situation
that needs your attention.

190
00:08:00.354 --> 00:08:01.647
It's Dyson and Travis.

191
00:08:01.731 --> 00:08:05.193
Oh. is this because I keep mixing up
their names because I got a trick now.

192
00:08:05.276 --> 00:08:06.527
Dyson is Black.

193
00:08:06.611 --> 00:08:07.612
Travis is white.

194
00:08:07.695 --> 00:08:09.197
-That's a good trick.
-Like the cookie.

195
00:08:09.280 --> 00:08:11.449
Norm. Dyson and Travis hate each other

196
00:08:11.532 --> 00:08:14.327
because they're fighting over this girl.
Zoé Debay.

197
00:08:14.410 --> 00:08:16.329
Wait. wait. wait. from Triple Trouble?

198
00:08:16.412 --> 00:08:17.955
Oh. I used to love that show.

199
00:08:18.039 --> 00:08:21.584
I'd watch that with my daughter.
Then she married that son of a bitch.

200
00:08:22.168 --> 00:08:24.545
He's… he's an indoor rock climber.

201
00:08:24.629 --> 00:08:27.632
-I need you to talk to them and fix it.
-To who? The triplets?

202
00:08:27.715 --> 00:08:30.218
-You know that's one girl. right?
-The players. Norm.

203
00:08:30.301 --> 00:08:33.346
-What are you going to say to them?
-Okay. yeah. I get it.

204
00:08:33.930 --> 00:08:36.265
I got a thing that always works.

205
00:08:37.266 --> 00:08:43.898
Just… just make sure you come to practice.
and… and I'll put the pieces together.

206
00:08:43.981 --> 00:08:45.650
[upbeat music playing]

207
00:08:45.733 --> 00:08:46.651
♪ Yeah ♪

208
00:08:46.734 --> 00:08:47.818
♪ Turn it up ♪

209
00:08:48.861 --> 00:08:49.904
♪ Yeah ♪

210
00:08:49.987 --> 00:08:51.113
-[whistle blows]
-Bring it in.

211
00:08:51.197 --> 00:08:52.240
Let's go. hustle up.

212
00:08:53.783 --> 00:08:55.576
-Bring it in.
-[assistant coach] Let's go.

213
00:08:55.660 --> 00:08:56.994
-Hold this.
-Yeah.

214
00:08:57.078 --> 00:08:59.330
Okay. gentlemen.
it's come to my attention that…

215
00:08:59.413 --> 00:09:02.208
[clears throat] …there's some trouble
in the locker room. Huh?

216
00:09:02.291 --> 00:09:03.876
Maybe over a woman.

217
00:09:04.460 --> 00:09:06.629
The point is
we're gonna nip it in the bud.

218
00:09:06.712 --> 00:09:07.630
Hold that up.

219
00:09:09.590 --> 00:09:10.883
Tell me what you see here.

220
00:09:11.467 --> 00:09:12.760
Golden Gate Bridge.

221
00:09:12.843 --> 00:09:13.803
Wrong.

222
00:09:15.638 --> 00:09:16.931
It's a metaphor.

223
00:09:17.014 --> 00:09:19.892
I mean. yeah. yeah.
it… it is the Golden Gate Bridge.

224
00:09:20.393 --> 00:09:23.104
And a lot of brave Italians
lost their lives trying to build it.

225
00:09:23.187 --> 00:09:27.817
What I'm trying to get at is this puzzle
could be the fucking championship

226
00:09:27.900 --> 00:09:33.281
if we just bridge our differences
and work together. Heh?

227
00:09:33.364 --> 00:09:36.075
Okay. now is there something wrong
with this puzzle?

228
00:09:37.702 --> 00:09:38.536
Travis?

229
00:09:38.619 --> 00:09:40.746
I mean. obviously two pieces are missing.

230
00:09:40.830 --> 00:09:42.957
My man! Yes!

231
00:09:43.708 --> 00:09:45.710
There's two pieces missing.

232
00:09:46.210 --> 00:09:49.130
Travis… this is you.

233
00:09:53.092 --> 00:09:55.845
Dyson… this is you.

234
00:09:57.555 --> 00:09:58.806
You go right in there.

235
00:09:58.889 --> 00:09:59.890
[assistant coach] Mm-hmm.

236
00:10:00.600 --> 00:10:02.727
-Hold on. He goes in there.
-Yeah.

237
00:10:02.810 --> 00:10:03.936
No. it's not going in.

238
00:10:04.020 --> 00:10:05.605
-It's upside down.
-[Norm] It's not.

239
00:10:05.688 --> 00:10:07.982
-Rotate it. It's gonna fit.
-The little part's on the top.

240
00:10:08.065 --> 00:10:10.901
-That corner works.
-Doesn't matter. Here's the point.

241
00:10:10.985 --> 00:10:15.031
You two. you gotta stop pretending
like you don't fit together.

242
00:10:16.282 --> 00:10:17.450
-Give me.
-Sure.

243
00:10:17.533 --> 00:10:19.368
-No. the ball. The ball.
-Here you go.

244
00:10:19.452 --> 00:10:21.495
Listen. we're gonna do
